TITLE: Initializing and Using ComponentClient in Akka Java SDK
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to inject and use the ComponentClient to make calls between components in an Akka service. It shows the constructor injection, request building, and response handling.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka-sdk/blob/main/samples/ask-akka-agent/src/main/resources/flat-doc/component-and-service-calls.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
public class ShoppingCartEndpoint {
    private final ComponentClient componentClient;

    public ShoppingCartEndpoint(ComponentClient componentClient) {
        this.componentClient = componentClient;
    }

    public CompletionStage<HttpResponse> addItem(AddLineItem command) {
        return componentClient
                .forEventSourcedEntity(command.getCartId())
                .call(ShoppingCart::addItem)
                .params(command)
                .execute()
                .thenApply(reply -> HttpResponse.ok());
    }
}
```

