TITLE: Defining View to Consume Events from Event Sourced Entity in Java
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to define a View that consumes events from an Event Sourced Entity. It includes a handler method for processing different types of CustomerEvents.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka-sdk/blob/main/samples/ask-akka-agent/src/main/resources/flat-doc/views.md#2025-04-22_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
package customer.application;

import akka.javasdk.annotations.ComponentId;
import akka.javasdk.annotations.Subscribe;
import akka.javasdk.view.View;

@ComponentId("customers-by-name")
public class CustomerByNameView extends View<CustomerRow> {

  @Subscribe.EventSourcedEntity
  public CustomerEntity customerEntity;

  public TableUpdater<CustomerRow> tableUpdater;

  @EventHandler
  public Effect<CustomerRow> onEvent(CustomerEvent event) {
    String customerId = eventSubject();
    return switch (event) {
      case CustomerCreated c -> effects().updateRow(
          new CustomerRow(customerId, c.name(), c.email()));
      case CustomerNameChanged c -> effects().updateRow(
          row -> row.withName(c.newName()));
      case CustomerEmailChanged c -> effects().updateRow(
          row -> row.withEmail(c.newEmail()));
      case CustomerAddressChanged ignored -> effects().ignore();
    };
  }
}
```

