TITLE: Implementing State Update Logic in Java
DESCRIPTION: Defines the addItem method in the ShoppingCart class to update the state when a new item is added. Handles both new and existing items.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka-sdk/blob/main/samples/ask-akka-agent/src/main/resources/flat-doc/event-sourced-entities.md#2025-04-22_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
public ShoppingCart addItem(String productId, String name, int quantity, BigDecimal price) {
  List<LineItem> updatedItems = new ArrayList<>(items);
  Optional<LineItem> existingItem = items.stream()
      .filter(item -> item.productId().equals(productId))
      .findFirst();

  if (existingItem.isPresent()) {
    LineItem item = existingItem.get();
    updatedItems.remove(item);
    item = new LineItem(productId, name, item.quantity() + quantity, price);
    updatedItems.add(item);
  } else {
    updatedItems.add(new LineItem(productId, name, quantity, price));
  }

  return new ShoppingCart(cartId, updatedItems);
}
```

