TITLE: Implementing Custom Dependency Injection in Tests
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to provide mock dependencies in tests using a custom DependencyProvider with TestKit. This allows for isolated testing of components with controlled dependencies.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka-sdk/blob/main/samples/ask-akka-agent/src/main/resources/flat-doc/setup-and-dependency-injection.md#2025-04-22_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
@Test
public void testWithCustomDependencies() {
  // Create mock dependencies
  MyAppSettings mockSettings = mock(MyAppSettings.class);
  when(mockSettings.getSomeSetting()).thenReturn("test-value");

  // Create a custom DependencyProvider that returns the mocks
  DependencyProvider testProvider = new DependencyProvider() {
    @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
    @Override
    public <T> T lookup(Class<T> clazz) {
      if (clazz.equals(MyAppSettings.class)) {
        return (T) mockSettings;
      } else {
        return null;
      }
    }
  };

  TestKit testKit = TestKit.of(TestKit.Settings.create().withDependencyProvider(testProvider));

  // Use testKit to interact with components that will get the mocked dependencies
}
```

