TITLE: Updating State in Key Value Entity in Java
DESCRIPTION: Implementation of command handlers for updating state in a Key Value Entity, demonstrating how to set a new value and increment the counter using the Effect API.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka-sdk/blob/main/samples/ask-akka-agent/src/main/resources/flat-doc/key-value-entities.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
public Effect<Counter> set(int newValue) {
  Counter newState = new Counter(newValue); // 1
  return effects()
      .updateState(newState)
      .thenReply(newState); // 2
}

public Effect<Counter> plusOne() {
  Counter newState = new Counter(currentState().value() + 1); // 3
  return effects()
      .updateState(newState)
      .thenReply(newState); // 4
}
```

