TITLE: Calling Other Akka Services Using HttpClientProvider in Java
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to use HttpClientProvider to call other Akka services within the same project. It demonstrates constructor injection, client lookup, and making a REST call to another service.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka-sdk/blob/main/samples/ask-akka-agent/src/main/resources/flat-doc/component-and-service-calls.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
public class DelegatingServiceEndpoint {
    private final HttpClient counterClient;

    public DelegatingServiceEndpoint(HttpClientProvider clientProvider) {
        this.counterClient = clientProvider.httpClientFor("counter");
    }

    public CompletionStage<HttpResponse> increment(String id) {
        return counterClient
                .post("/counter/" + id + "/increment")
                .withEmptyRequest()
                .execute()
                .thenApply(response -> {
                    if (response.status() == 200) {
                        return HttpResponse.ok();
                    } else {
                        return HttpResponse.internalServerError();
                    }
                });
    }
}
```

