TITLE: Scheduling Timer in OrderEndpoint
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to schedule a timer in the OrderEndpoint class using TimerScheduler and ComponentClient. It shows the process of generating a unique timer ID, registering the timer, and composing it with an order placement call.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka-sdk/blob/main/samples/ask-akka-agent/src/main/resources/flat-doc/timed-actions.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
public class OrderEndpoint {

  private final TimerScheduler timerScheduler; // 1
  private final ComponentClient componentClient;

  @Inject
  public OrderEndpoint(TimerScheduler timerScheduler, ComponentClient componentClient) {
    this.timerScheduler = timerScheduler;
    this.componentClient = componentClient;
  }

  public Effect<Done> placeOrder(PlaceOrder command) {
    String orderId = UUID.randomUUID().toString(); // 2

    CompletionStage<Done> timerRegistration =
        timerScheduler.startSingleTimer( // 3
            "order-expiration-" + orderId, // 4
            Duration.ofMinutes(5), // 5
            OrderTimedAction.class, // 6
            "expireOrder",
            new ExpireOrder(orderId));

    return effects()
        .asyncReply(
            timerRegistration
                .thenCompose(
                    done ->
                        componentClient
                            .forKeyValueEntity(orderId)
                            .call(OrderEntity::placeOrder)
                            .execute(new PlaceOrder(orderId, command.item()))) // 7
                .thenApply(reply -> Done.done()));
  }
}
```

