TITLE: Creating a View from a Topic with Metadata in Java
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how to create a View that consumes from a topic, including the addition of required metadata (ce-subject) for correct message consumption.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka-sdk/blob/main/samples/ask-akka-agent/src/main/resources/flat-doc/views.md#2025-04-22_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
package counter.application;

import akka.javasdk.annotations.Consume;
import akka.javasdk.annotations.Subscribe;
import akka.javasdk.view.View;

public class CounterJournalToTopicWithMetaConsumer extends View<CounterValue> {

  @Subscribe.EventSourcedEntity
  public CounterEntity counterEntity;

  @Consume.FromTopic("counter-topic")
  public Effect<CounterValue> consumeCounterIncremented(CounterIncremented event) {
    String counterIdAsSubject = "counter-" + eventSubject();
    return effects()
        .produce("counter-topic")
        .message(event)
        .metadata(Map.of("ce-subject", counterIdAsSubject));
  }
}
```

