TITLE: Unit Testing Key Value Entities in Java
DESCRIPTION: Example of using KeyValueEntityTestKit to unit test a Key Value Entity, demonstrating how to test setting values, incrementing counters, and verifying state changes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka-sdk/blob/main/samples/ask-akka-agent/src/main/resources/flat-doc/key-value-entities.md#2025-04-22_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
@Test
public void counterTest() {
  // 1. Create Entity test kit
  KeyValueEntityTestKit<Counter, CounterEntity> testKit =
      KeyValueEntityTestKit.of(CounterEntity::new);

  // 2. Call set method with value 10
  KeyValueEntityResult<Counter> result = testKit.call(e -> e.set(10));

  // 3. Assert the reply is 10
  assertEquals(10, result.getReply().value());

  // 4. Call plusOne and assert result is 11
  result = testKit.call(CounterEntity::plusOne);
  assertEquals(11, result.getReply().value());

  // 5. Assert the state is now 11
  assertEquals(11, testKit.getState().value());
}
```

