TITLE: Configuring Splunk HEC Exporter
DESCRIPTION: YAML and CLI configurations to set up Splunk HTTP Event Collector for exporting metrics and logs, including endpoint and token configuration.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka-sdk/blob/main/samples/ask-akka-agent/src/main/resources/flat-doc/observability-exports.md#2025-04-22_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: yaml
CODE:
```
default:
  splunkHec:
    endpoint: https://<my-trial-instance>.splunkcloud.com:8088/services/collector
    tokenSecret:
      name: my-splunk-token
      key: token
```

LANGUAGE: command line
CODE:
```
akka project observability set default splunk-hec \
  --endpoint https://<my-trial-instance>.splunkcloud.com:8088/services/collector \
  --token-secret-name my-splunk-token --token-secret-key token
```

