TITLE: Confirming Order and Deleting Timer
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to confirm an order and delete the associated timer in the OrderEndpoint class. It demonstrates the importance of sequence in confirming the order before canceling the timer.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka-sdk/blob/main/samples/ask-akka-agent/src/main/resources/flat-doc/timed-actions.md#2025-04-22_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
public class OrderEndpoint {

  public Effect<Done> confirmOrder(ConfirmOrder command) {
    return effects()
        .asyncReply(
            componentClient
                .forKeyValueEntity(command.orderId())
                .call(OrderEntity::confirm)
                .execute() // 1
                .thenCompose(
                    reply -> {
                      if (reply instanceof Ok) {
                        return timerScheduler.cancel("order-expiration-" + command.orderId()); // 2
                      } else {
                        return CompletableFuture.completedFuture(Done.done());
                      }
                    })
                .thenApply(done -> Done.done()));
  }
}
```

