TITLE: Cancelling Order in OrderEntity
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the cancel method in the OrderEntity class. It handles different scenarios such as when the order was never placed, is already confirmed, or can be successfully canceled.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka-sdk/blob/main/samples/ask-akka-agent/src/main/resources/flat-doc/timed-actions.md#2025-04-22_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
public class OrderEntity extends KeyValueEntity<OrderState> {

  public Effect<Reply> cancel() {
    return effects()
        .read()
        .thenReply(
            maybeState -> {
              if (maybeState.isEmpty()) { // 1
                return new NotFound();
              } else if (maybeState.get().confirmed()) { // 2
                return new Invalid("Order already confirmed");
              } else {
                return effects()
                    .updateState(OrderState.EMPTY) // 3
                    .thenReply(new Ok());
              }
            });
  }
}
```

