TITLE: Creating Docker Image for Antora Documentation Generation
DESCRIPTION: This Dockerfile sets up an Ubuntu-based image with Node.js, Antora, and various npm packages installed. It creates a non-root user 'jenkins' and sets up the working directory for documentation generation.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka-sdk/blob/main/docs/antora-docker/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: Dockerfile
CODE:
```
FROM ubuntu:22.04

RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y curl

# Install Node.js
RUN curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_18.x | bash -
RUN apt-get install -y nodejs

# Install Antora and required packages
RUN npm i -g @antora/cli@3.1 @antora/site-generator@3.1
RUN npm i -g @antora/lunr-extension@1.0.0-alpha.8

# Install additional npm packages
RUN npm install -g asciidoctor-kroki

# Create jenkins user
RUN useradd -m jenkins

# Set up working directory
RUN mkdir -p /opt/workspace && chown jenkins:jenkins /opt/workspace
WORKDIR /opt/workspace
USER jenkins

# Set the entrypoint
ENTRYPOINT ["/bin/bash"]

```
